# name.word — what a NAME is, has, and can. An identity, one who acts and signs.
# A Name (the identity) is always written Name in the Word. A being's name (its handle) and the
# verb to name are lowercase. Only the identity, the primitive here, is Name.
# Axiom. Bottoms out in the host (seed/materials/name/). The id IS an ed25519 public key, self-
# certifying (keys.js). The stamper signs the Name's acts with its held key (signingSession.js).
# The chain does not fork, identity is above histories (closure.js, name.js). Descends from
# word.word, iam.word, base.word, chain.word. Grounds `key` and `sign`, as base grounds `hash`.
# A Name's beings, the ones it acts through, are in being.word. The name verb is the Name's
# can, below. `connect` is shared with BE, the identity-layer of the one act, told apart by object.

A Name is one who acts, a facet of the I.
A Name has a key, its own secret. The Name's id is the key's open half, by which all may know the Name and none may be it.
To sign is to seal a fact with a key, so all may know which Name made it, and none may forge it.
A Name signs its every act.
A Name has act chains, one per being per history, the chains of its acts. A Name is one and the same above every history, the owner and signer of them all, not their key.
A Name may also have a name, a word read and said in place of its key.
A Name has a parent, a Name before it, back to the I.
The I is the first Name, the parent of all.
A Name can be declared, with a key new or already its own.
A Name can connect, and sign, and release.
A Name can export, and gives its key to the one who acts as it.
A Name can banish. Its chain seals.
